CATEGORY 1 — PII & PROFILE EXPOSURE          max  30 pts
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Full legal name visible on profile              12 pts
  → Real name makes a subject directly
    identifiable and searchable across
    platforms. Core input for impersonation
    and pretexting attacks.

Email address visible / inferrable              10 pts
  → Exposed email is the primary delivery
    channel for spear-phishing. Also enables
    attacker to craft believable "I know
    who you are" pretexts.

Date of birth visible                            8 pts
  → Combined with name: sufficient to
    construct a convincing identity claim,
    pass verbal verification (e.g. bank
    or telco calls), and personalise lures.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
CATEGORY 2 — ACCOUNT PRIVACY SETTINGS        max  15 pts
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Account set to Public                           10 pts
  → Entire post history, follower/following
    list, tagged content, and stories are
    freely accessible. Enables deep
    reconnaissance with no interaction
    required from the attacker.

Stories not restricted (no Close Friends use)    5 pts
  → Stories reveal daily context — location,
    mood, routines, social circle. No
    segmentation means this real-time feed
    is open to all followers including
    unknown/fake accounts.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
CATEGORY 3 — CONTENT & LOCATION EXPOSURE     max  30 pts
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Geotags enabled on posts / stories             12 pts
  → Directly exposes home address, workplace,
    and daily routine. Highest-value input
    for pattern-of-life analysis — lets an
    attacker predict where a subject will
    be and when.

Photos reveal home / workplace exterior        10 pts
  → Even without explicit tags, background
    details (street signs, storefronts,
    building features) allow geolocation.
    Provides physical context for
    in-person social engineering attempts.

Posts contain minors with identifying info       8 pts
  → School names, uniforms, children's
    routines create additional leverage
    points. Social engineers exploit family
    context to build urgency and emotional
    pressure in pretexting scenarios.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
CATEGORY 4 — CONNECTED ACCOUNTS & ACCESS     max  15 pts
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Facebook account linked / cross-posting          8 pts
  → Direct bridge to a second identity
    profile with richer PII (workplace,
    hometown, relationships, life events).
    An attacker researching Instagram can
    pivot to Facebook for a fuller picture.

3+ third-party apps connected via OAuth          7 pts
  → Publicly visible app connections signal
    what services the subject uses. Enables
    targeted platform-specific lures
    ("Your Spotify linked to Instagram
    has been flagged…").

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
CATEGORY 5 — ACCOUNT HYGIENE & HISTORY       max  10 pts
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Account inactive 12+ months but still public    6 pts
  → Dormant public accounts are prime
    impersonation targets — owner won't
    notice a cloned profile, and the post
    history provides authentic-looking
    material for a fake account.

Username exactly matches other platforms         4 pts
  → Trivial cross-platform correlation.
    Allows an attacker to aggregate profiles
    on LinkedIn, Twitter, Reddit, and
    GitHub from a single username, building
    a comprehensive target dossier.

